The paper discusses improving the performance of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on preventing overfitting by randomly omitting half of the feature detectors on each training case. This technique is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper primarily deals with neural networks and machine learning, cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
